name: Injera
description: A fermented flatbread made from teff flour, a staple in Ethiopian cuisine.

name: Shiro Wat
description: A thick stew made from chickpea flour, onions, garlic, and spices.

name: Doro Wat
description: A spicy chicken stew cooked with berbere spice and served with injera.

name: Kitfo
description: Ethiopian-style minced raw beef, often seasoned with mitmita and niter kibbeh.

name: Gomen
description: Collard greens sautéed with garlic, onions, and spices.

name: Misir Wat
description: A red lentil stew cooked with berbere spice and onions.

name: Tibs
description: Sautéed beef or lamb with onions, garlic, and Ethiopian spices.

name: Firfir
description: A dish made from shredded injera mixed with berbere and spiced butter.

name: Chechebsa
description: A wheat-based breakfast dish sautéed with butter and berbere.

name: Atmit
description: A traditional porridge drink made from barley flour, sugar, and milk.

name: Genfo
description: A thick porridge made from barley flour and served with spiced butter.

name: Bula
description: A porridge-like dish made from enset (false banana) starch.

name: Kolo
description: Roasted barley or other grains, often mixed with peanuts and spices.

name: Fasolia
description: A dish made from green beans and carrots sautéed with onions and spices.

name: Ayib
description: Ethiopian cottage cheese, often served as a side with spicy dishes.

name: Dabo
description: Traditional Ethiopian bread, usually baked from wheat or barley flour.

name: Tej
description: A traditional Ethiopian honey wine, often home-brewed and served in a berele.

name: Beso
description: A traditional Ethiopian energy snack made from roasted barley flour mixed with honey or milk.
